article.description: Mwadi Mabika scored 17 points, including the winning putback with 26.5 seconds left, to lead the defending WNBA champion Los Angeles Sparks to a 69-65 victory over the Miami Sol on Thursday night.
article.headline: Sparks use 23-6 run to rally past Sol
article.linkText: Slow-starting Sparks rally to eclipse Sol
article.story:
MIAMI (AP) -- Mwadi Mabika scored 17 points, including the winning putback with 26.5 seconds left, to lead the defending WNBA champion Los Angeles Sparks to a 69-65 victory over the Miami Sol on Thursday night. The Sol (0-2) had a chance to take the lead or force overtime in the final seconds, but Nikki Teasley stripped the ball from Sandy Brondello with 3.2 seconds left and made two free throws. "We're trying to understand what it takes to repeat as a champion,'' Sparks coach Michael Cooper said. "Games like this will help. As the saying goes, champions find a way to win, and that's what we did.'' Miami's two losses have been by a total of seven points. In those games, the Sol have shot only 64 percent from the foul line and have been outrebounded 44-22 on the defensive end. "There are no moral victories in this league,'' Sol coach Ron Rothstein said. "We've lost two games at the end. They have to learn how to win a close game. That's the bottom line.'' After falling behind 39-31 with 18:11 to play, Los Angeles used a 23-6 run -- capped by Tamecka Dixon's jumper -- to take a 54-45 lead with 9:13 to go. "It was a tough one for us,'' Dixon said. "This was one we really had to get up for. We weren't up in the beginning.'' Brondello scored 10 of her 20 points in the final 6:59, including two free throws with 1:15 left to give the Sol their last lead, 64-63. Dixon added 13 points for Los Angeles (3-0). Lisa Leslie, who scored 36 points in the Sparks' first two games of the season, had eight points and fouled out with 1:32 remaining. "That's why it hurts so bad, because we got her out and didn't take advantage of it,'' Miami's Pollyana Kimbrough said. "It's a tough one to lose.'' Sheri Sam had 13 points and Kimbrough had 12 points and eight rebounds for the Sol.

Game notes
Los Angeles has trailed at halftime in both of its games against Eastern Conference teams this season. ... Sam has missed 18 of 27 shots from the field in the Sol's two games. ... Los Angeles outrebounded Miami 36-26. ... The game was delayed by 12 minutes in the first half because of a shot-clock malfunction. ... The crowd of 7,320 was 1,180 larger than the announced attendance for the Marlins-Reds baseball game, also in Miami.
